        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 5:07PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 26
miles northwest of Persimmon Gap, or 38 miles south of Alpine, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Santiago Peak.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
